# orcasecurity_integration_pagerduty (Resource)

Manages a [PagerDuty](https://www.pagerduty.com/) integration in Orca Security.

Under the hood this creates an entry under `POST /api/external_service/config`
with `service_name = "pagerduty"`. The integration key is stored in Orca's
secret store and is never returned by the API.

## Example Usage

### Basic example

{{tffile "examples/resources/orcasecurity_integration_pagerduty/resource.tf"}}

### Sourcing the integration key from HashiCorp Vault

```terraform
data "vault_generic_secret" "pd" {
  path = "secret/pagerduty/orca"
}

resource "orcasecurity_integration_pagerduty" "from_vault" {
  template_name   = "pager_duty"
  integration_key = data.vault_generic_secret.pd.data["integration_key"]
}
```

### Sourcing the integration key from a Kubernetes Secret

```terraform
data "kubernetes_secret" "pd" {
  metadata {
    name      = "pagerduty-creds"
    namespace = "orca"
  }
}

resource "orcasecurity_integration_pagerduty" "from_k8s" {
  template_name   = "pager_duty"
  integration_key = data.kubernetes_secret.pd.data["integration_key"]
}
```

## Argument Reference

* `template_name` — (Required, String) Identifier for the integration as shown
  in the Orca UI and used as the lookup key for update/delete operations.
  Changing this forces a new resource.
* `integration_key` — (Required, String, Sensitive) PagerDuty Events API V2
  integration key. Stored in Orca's secret store; never returned by the API.
* `is_enabled` — (Optional, Bool) Whether the integration is enabled. Defaults
  to `true`.
* `is_default` — (Optional, Bool) Whether this integration is the
  organisation's default PagerDuty configuration. Defaults to `false`.

## Attribute Reference

* `id` — (String) Orca external service config identifier (UUID).

## Notes

* The Orca API strips `integration_key` from `GET` responses (the value lives
  in SSM). The provider keeps the value already stored in Terraform state to
  avoid a permanent diff. Rotate through `terraform apply`; for out-of-band
  rotation use `terraform apply -replace=orcasecurity_integration_pagerduty.example`.
* Use an encrypted remote backend (S3 + KMS, GCS, Terraform Cloud, etc.) and
  restrict read access to the state — the integration key lands in state
  regardless of the `sensitive = true` flag on the attribute.

## Import

PagerDuty integrations can be imported by their `template_name`:

```bash
terraform import orcasecurity_integration_pagerduty.example pager_duty
```

After import, set the `integration_key` argument in your configuration — the
API does not return it.

